HEADWORD: Magna Mater
<hw>Magna Mater</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A great nature goddess of
ancient Phrygia in Asia Minor; the counterpart of the Greek
<altname>Rhea</altname> and the Roman <altname>Ops</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Cybele, Dindymene, Great Mother, Mater
Turrita.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magnanimity</ent>⟦br⟧
